content: I don't have personal preferences, but there are many iconic duke ellington songs that are considered classics and are beloved by many people. some of his most famous compositions include "take the a train," "mood indigo," "it don't mean a thing (if it ain't got that swing)," and "sophisticated lady." these songs showcase ellington's mastery of harmony, melody, and rhythm, as well as his skill at arranging for big band ensembles. each song has a unique personality and feel, but they all share a sense of swing and improvisation that is at the heart of jazz music.
